<div class="subhead" style="padding-top:3px; padding-bottom:7px">Behind the Scenes at CES</div>
<span class="text">
Check out <EM>Behind the Scenes at CES </EM>for updates on the extra efforts the International CES makes to improve the show and make your experience better. <BR><A name=scene1></A>
<P><STRONG>Wireless Access Point Blocking at the LVCC<BR></STRONG>Important! Smart City, the exclusive provider of Internet Service at the Las Vegas Convention Center (LVCC), has installed a new Air-magnet System to help manage the wireless network in the building. </P>
<P>This Air-magnet system will provide numerous reports that inform Smart City how the wireless network is running. It will also indicate when someone brings in their own “access point” (AP) and a general idea of where it is located inside the exhibit hall. To circumvent network disruption, this air-magnet system provides the ability to turn off these APs remotely, known as “blocking.” </P>
<P><STRONG>Therefore, if you plan to utilize some type of access point in the convention center, it is imperative that you notify </STRONG><STRONG>Smart</STRONG><STRONG></STRONG><STRONG> City</STRONG><STRONG> three weeks in advance of the show. This will help to achieve optimum performance and avoid blocking of your access point.</STRONG><STRONG></STRONG></P>
<P>Note: This “blocking” will only affect access points, not other products that use the 2.4 frequency. Look for more details on products that use the 2.4 frequency in a future issue of the <EM>Exhibitor’s Source</EM>. </P><A name=scene2></A>
<P><STRONG>CEA Media Tour Promotion<BR></STRONG>To get a jump on promoting the 2005 show, CES is teaming up with the Las Vegas Convention and Visitors Authority (LVCVA) and several other large Las Vegas tradeshows for the first ever South American road show. </P>
<P>South America is a bustling international market,&nbsp;and we&nbsp;want their business!&nbsp;We're reaching out to business and consumer press in South America and talking to buyers in an effort to increase&nbsp;attendance at the 2005 International CES. The event will be held in Sao Paulo, Brazil, September 13-17, 2004, and is the first official press event of the 2005 International CES season.&nbsp; </P><A name=scene3></A>
<P><STRONG>Protecting Your E-mail Address<BR></STRONG>We’re sensitive to the amount of e-mail messages you receive each day and do not release your address to any outside parties. In an effort to address unsolicited messages that you might see as “spam,” we have set up a <A href="mailto:DoNotSpam@ce.org">DoNotSpam@ce.org</A> mailbox. </P>
<P>If you feel you have received an unsolicited message from a party outside the International CES, forward the message to <A href="mailto:DoNotSpam@ce.org">DoNotSpam@ce.org</A>. You will receive an automatic e-mail response, defining the parameters of legitimate e-mail messages, along with copy you can use to respond to the unwanted message. </P><A name=testing></A>Through this monthly <EM>Exhibitor’s Source</EM> newsletter, the International CES communicates important exhibitor information on the first Tuesday of each month. You may occasionally receive an <EM>Exhibitor’s Source Update</EM> with an important intermittent announcement. Any additional messages from International CES partner organizations are mailed on their behalf, and they do not receive direct access to our exhibitor lists.
</span>
