<div class="subhead" style="padding-top:3px; padding-bottom:7px">CES Unveiled: The Official Press Event of the International CES</div>
<span class="text">
It's bigger and better. And it's a press event like no other. Right before the International CES opens. 4–7 p.m. Tuesday, January 4, 2005, in the Las Vegas Convention Center Room S226 is your chance to meet the top names in international trade and consumer press—print, broadcast and online.&nbsp; 
<P><IMG height=49 src="/print/images/general/CES_Unveiled_event.gif" width=250 align=right>Meet the press in one easy location, while the event is filmed for CES’ satellite video news release for distribution to broadcast stations nationwide. </P>
<P>Media and analysts also will get a sneak peek at the Innovations Design and Engineering Showcase honorees and the 2005 International CES product debuts during <EM>CES Unveiled: The Official Press Event of the International CES</EM>. Media and analysts will enjoy cocktails and hors d’oeuvres, while checking out tabletop demonstrations and networking with Innovations honorees and CES exhibitors. </P>
<P>Participants receive:</P>
<UL>
<LI>Access to more than 350 credentialed media and analysts in attendance </LI>
<LI>Free contact lists of pre-registered and confirmed media/analysts </LI>
<LI>A 50-word description and logo in the press event program guide </LI>
<LI>Extensive pre-show promotion to CES’ worldwide media list via Web, e-mail, news wires, print materials and direct individual pitching </LI>
<LI>Your product displayed among the Innovations 2005 Honorees’ products—a <EM>must see</EM> for press and analysts! </LI>
<LI>Four exhibitor passes to the event </LI>
<LI>One 6-foot draped exhibit table </LI>
<LI>500 watts of electrical service </LI>
<LI>44”x 7” sign for your tabletop </LI>
<LI>High-speed Internet access </LI>
<LI>Telephone lines and A/V equipment available </LI></UL>
<P>2004 CES Press Event attendees included editors from <EM>NBC Today Show, </EM>CNN, ABC News, Bloomberg News, <EM>Business Week, Wired, Maxim </EM>and <EM>Rolling Stone. </EM></P>Only credentialed media and analysts are allowed to attend this exclusive CEA-sponsored event. Make sure you’re there! Interested exhibitors should contact Ryan Strowger, Manager, Business Development, CEA at <A href="mailto:rstrowger@ce.org">rstrowger@ce.org</A> or 703-907-7679.
</span>
