    <p><strong>Upcoming Exhibitor Workshop </strong><br> by Dan Cole</p>
    I remember the first time I got up in front of a public audience to speak: college speech class. Five minutes, and I had to tell 50 classmates about Bruce Springsteen—someone I knew little about, although I loved his music. It was the longest 300 seconds of my life, and I thought I would die. 
<P>I didn’t, but with time, I did learn that with practice it gets easier. And I also learned that there’s nothing to fear once the unknown is pulled out of the equation. If you know what you’re talking about—if you know what you’re doing—there’s nothing to sweat. </P>
<P>That’s why I think the free workshop coming up in September is such a great resource for International CES exhibitors. Spending a day at the Las Vegas Convention Center with an experienced CES team and many of the show’s vendors builds confidence and the expertise you need and also takes all of the guesswork out of your exhibit experience. </P>
<P>It’s free, the hotel’s only $59, and believe me, it’s worth the time and trip for new and ‘old’ exhibitors, alike. For first timers, it’s all about learning and ROI. And for the old pros, it’s all about getting deep discounts on anything you may need (another perk for first timers as well, of course). </P>
<P>There’s not much time left to register, though; the deadline is August 20. So register now, and you can also check out the agenda and other detailed information about what we have lined up for you. </P>
<P>And, unfortunately for me, Springsteen ain't coming to Washington this summer. </P>
<P>‘Hope to see you September 21 in Las Vegas at the Exhibitor Workshop. </P>
